An 11-year-old child died after drowning in a pool in a country club on the KZN North Coast. IPSS medical rescue and SAPS responded to the scene. According to a statement released by IPSS, it is alleged that two children entered the property to swim in the pool on Monday. Meanwhile, both the country club and the pool were closed at the time. “One child got into difficulty, disappearing under the water and the second child returned home to get help, despite the best efforts of IPSS Medical and all on scene, the resuscitation was unsuccessful,” said Dylan Meyrick of IPSS Medical Response. In another incident, the search continues for a 74-year-old man who got swept away by sea while he was fishing at a Durban beach on Monday afternoon. According to Paul Herbst of Medi Response, the man got swept away while trying to cross the canal at Cuttings Beach, south of Durban. Medi Response search and rescue unit, together with SAPS were on scene. “Witnesses report that they saw the man drown before disappearing from site. “Searches were undertaken with negative results and have been suspended due to lack of light,” said Herbst.